<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species is transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hopkins" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Arixyleborus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Arixyleborus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Arixyleborus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lea" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Amasa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Amasa" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Amasa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species displays a superficial morphological resemblance to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lea" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Amasa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Amasa" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Amasa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however it possesses the unique characteristics exhibited by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hopkins" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Arixyleborus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Arixyleborus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Arixyleborus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
including protibiae slender, inflated and granulate on posterior faces, antennal club type 2, six striae present on the declivity, and pronotum from dorsal view elongated basic shape with rounded frontal margin (type 7).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
